    "4) VAE loss function\n",
    "\n",
    "The VAE objective consists of two terms:\n",
    "- Reconstruction loss: How well the output matches the input\n",
    "- KL divergence: Forces latent distribution close to N(0, I)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
<<<<<<< HEAD
   "execution_count": 5,
=======
   "execution_count": 4,
>>>>>>> bce8a398e16739e5c63188f88a3fb48b02aa3efa
   "id": "0c9459ee",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "def vae_loss(x, x_hat, mu, logvar):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    x      : original images\n",
    "    x_hat  : reconstructed images\n",
    "    mu     : latent mean\n",
    "    logvar : latent log-variance\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Reconstruction loss:\n",
    "    # Binary cross-entropy works well for MNIST\n",
    "    recon_loss = nn.functional.binary_cross_entropy(\n",
    "        x_hat, x, reduction=\"sum\"\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "    # KL divergence between:\n",
    "    # q(z|x) = N(mu, sigma^2)\n",
    "    # p(z)   = N(0, I)\n",
    "    kl_div = -0.5 * torch.sum(\n",
    "        1 + logvar - mu.pow(2) - logvar.exp()\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Total VAE loss\n",
    "    return recon_loss + kl_div"
   ]
  },
